    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I believe processing attestations in RPC was an artifact of the past we used as a \"patch\" to prevent justified epoch off-by-one errors. I believe this is mitigated by having new core logic, revamped fork choice, and an overall stronger runtime that we should not need to do this in many different places.",
